{# The Pledge — the honest affiliate policy block.

   Drop this partial into any article layout near the bottom:
       {% include "partials/pledge.njk" %}

   On hub / index pages, opt into the wide treatment by setting
   the variant to "wide":
       {% set pledgeVariant = "wide" %}
       {% include "partials/pledge.njk" %}
#}

{% set _variant = pledgeVariant or "inline" %}

<aside class="pledge pledge--{{ _variant }}" aria-label="How we stay free">
  <div class="pledge-grid">
    {% if _variant == "wide" %}
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">&sect; The Pledge</span>
        <h2>The honest<br><span class="italic">affiliate</span><br>policy.</h2>
      </div>
    {% else %}
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">How we stay free</span>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

    <div>
      <p class="pledge-lede">
        We use affiliate codes &mdash; but only when they&rsquo;re actually
        the better deal.
      </p>
      <p class="pledge-body">
        If a vendor is running a 30%-off weekend and our code only earns
        you 15%, we point you to the sale &mdash; not our link. When our code
        <em>is</em> the better deal, you&rsquo;ll see it labeled, and using
        it costs you nothing extra.
      </p>
      <p class="pledge-body">
        The small commission those codes earn &mdash; when they earn
        anything &mdash; is what keeps the Lab free to use, ad-free, and
        beholden to no vendor.
      </p>
      <div class="pledge-promises">
        <span>&check; Best deal wins, always</span>
        <span>&check; Codes labeled in-line</span>
        <span>&check; No sponsored placement</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</aside>
